Use the QFile constructor or setFileName() before open(). Combine QIODeviceBase flags with |.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QFile file("config.ini");
if (file.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly | QIODevice::Text))
{
    QTextStream in(&file);
    QString content = in.readAll();
    file.close();
}
```

Use atEnd() in a loop. A maxlen of 0 disables the explicit length limit.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QFile file("config.txt");
if (!file.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly | QIODevice::Text))
    return;
QTextStream stream(&file);
stream.setEncoding(QStringConverter::Utf8);
while (!stream.atEnd())
    qDebug() << stream.readLine();
```

Set an explicit version for durable files or communication protocols so writer and reader agree on encoding rules.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QFile file("telemetry.bin");
if (file.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly))
{
    QDataStream out(&file);
    out.setVersion(QDataStream::Qt_6_5);
    out << quint32(0xAA55) << QStringLiteral("ready") << double(24.5);
}
```

