Qt APIs use both exclusive enumeration values and `QFlags` masks. JC Lib now documents every advanced choice and enables multi-selection only for compatible mask-style parameters.

Examples:
- exclusive enum: `Qt::PreciseTimer`;
- QFlags mask: `QFileDialog::DontUseNativeDialog | QFileDialog::ReadOnly`;
- QIODevice mask: `QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text`;
- QML buttons: `Dialog.Ok | Dialog.Cancel`.

Do not combine values when the popup remains single-selection: those entries model mutually exclusive behaviors or controlled presets.

