functions.longDescription:
Use QUrl::fromLocalFile() for local filesystem paths. Attach an audio output and, for video, a video widget or video sink before starting playback.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *player = new QMediaPlayer(this);
auto *audioOutput = new QAudioOutput(this);
auto *videoWidget = new QVideoWidget(this);
player->setAudioOutput(audioOutput);
player->setVideoOutput(videoWidget);
player->setSource(QUrl::fromLocalFile(videoPath));
audioOutput->setVolume(0.7);
videoWidget->show();
player->play();
```

Enumerate outputs with QMediaDevices::audioOutputs(), then assign the selected QAudioDevice before playback.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *player = new QMediaPlayer(this);
auto *audioOutput = new QAudioOutput(this);
player->setAudioOutput(audioOutput);

const auto outputs = QMediaDevices::audioOutputs();
if (!outputs.isEmpty())
    audioOutput->setDevice(outputs.first());
audioOutput->setVolume(0.5);
```

For widget-based applications, pass a QVideoWidget. The retained workflow shows the minimal preview wiring.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *player = new QMediaPlayer(this);
auto *videoWidget = new QVideoWidget(this);
player->setVideoOutput(videoWidget);
videoWidget->show();
```

A QMediaCaptureSession links camera, microphone, recorder, image capture and preview outputs. The retained workflow shows a live widget preview.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *camera = new QCamera(this);
auto *captureSession = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);
auto *videoWidget = new QVideoWidget(this);

captureSession->setCamera(camera);
captureSession->setVideoOutput(videoWidget);
videoWidget->show();
camera->start();
```

The returned capture identifier is reported again by asynchronous QImageCapture signals. Ensure the image-capture object belongs to the active capture session.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *camera = new QCamera(this);
auto *captureSession = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);
auto *imageCapture = new QImageCapture(this);
auto *viewfinder = new QVideoWidget(this);

captureSession->setCamera(camera);
captureSession->setVideoOutput(viewfinder);
captureSession->setImageCapture(imageCapture);
connect(imageCapture, &QImageCapture::imageSaved, this, [](int, const QString &fileName)
{
    qDebug() << "Saved" << fileName;
});

camera->start();
imageCapture->captureToFile();
```

Use this before starting QMediaRecorder when the recording pipeline needs microphone audio.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *audioInput = new QAudioInput(this);
auto *recorder = new QMediaRecorder(this);
auto *session = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);

session->setAudioInput(audioInput);
session->setRecorder(recorder);
recorder->setOutputLocation(QUrl::fromLocalFile(outputPath));
recorder->record();
```

Configure the capture session, recorder output URL and quality before starting. Recording state changes are asynchronous.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *camera = new QCamera(this);
auto *recorder = new QMediaRecorder(this);
auto *session = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);
auto *viewfinder = new QVideoWidget(this);

session->setCamera(camera);
session->setRecorder(recorder);
session->setVideoOutput(viewfinder);
recorder->setOutputLocation(QUrl::fromLocalFile(videoPath));
viewfinder->show();
camera->start();
recorder->record();
```

The retained workflow shows a complete audio-video recording pipeline with camera, microphone, recorder and preview output.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *camera = new QCamera(this);
auto *audioInput = new QAudioInput(this);
auto *recorder = new QMediaRecorder(this);
auto *session = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);
auto *preview = new QVideoWidget(this);

session->setCamera(camera);
session->setAudioInput(audioInput);
session->setRecorder(recorder);
session->setVideoOutput(preview);
preview->show();
camera->start();
```

QSoundEffect is intended for low-latency playback of short uncompressed audio effects. The retained workflow includes volume and playback.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *effect = new QSoundEffect(this);
effect->setSource(QUrl("qrc:/sounds/notify.wav"));
effect->setLoopCount(1);
effect->setVolume(0.4f);
effect->play();
```

Attach QAudioOutput and set a source first. The retained workflow shows a complete local audio-player setup.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *player = new QMediaPlayer(this);
auto *audio = new QAudioOutput(this);
player->setAudioOutput(audio);
player->setSource(QUrl::fromLocalFile(audioPath));
audio->setVolume(0.6);
player->play();
```

Use the returned QAudioDevice objects to populate a selector and call QAudioOutput::setDevice().

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
const auto outputs = QMediaDevices::audioOutputs();
for (const QAudioDevice &device : outputs) {
    if (device.description().contains("USB", Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
        auto *audio = new QAudioOutput(device, this);
        player->setAudioOutput(audio);
        break;
    }
}
```

The retained workflow shows how to place QAudioDevice values into a combo box while presenting their descriptions.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
ui->comboAudioOut->clear();
const auto outputs = QMediaDevices::audioOutputs();
for (const QAudioDevice &device : outputs)
    ui->comboAudioOut->addItem(device.description());
```

The retained workflow shows how to map an integer UI slider to the floating-point Qt Multimedia volume range.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *audio = new QAudioOutput(this);
connect(ui->sliderVolume, &QSlider::valueChanged, this, [audio](int value) {
    audio->setVolume(value / 100.0);
});
```

The retained workflow shows how to update and drive a position slider through positionChanged and setPosition().

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
connect(player, &QMediaPlayer::positionChanged, this, [this](qint64 pos) {
    ui->sliderPosition->setValue(static_cast<int>(pos));
});
connect(player, &QMediaPlayer::durationChanged, this, [this](qint64 dur) {
    ui->sliderPosition->setRange(0, static_cast<int>(dur));
});
```

Use a QUrl literal for network streams. Actual streaming support depends on the multimedia backend and platform codecs.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *player = new QMediaPlayer(this);
auto *audio = new QAudioOutput(this);
player->setAudioOutput(audio);
player->setSource(QUrl("https://example.com/radio.mp3"));
player->play();
```

Enumerate QMediaDevices::audioInputs(), choose one QAudioDevice and attach the QAudioInput to a capture session.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *audioInput = new QAudioInput(this);
auto *recorder = new QMediaRecorder(this);
auto *session = new QMediaCaptureSession(this);
session->setAudioInput(audioInput);
session->setRecorder(recorder);
recorder->setOutputLocation(QUrl::fromLocalFile(outputFile));
recorder->record();
```

The retained workflow shows how to populate a combo box with microphone descriptions and preserve each QAudioDevice value.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
ui->comboAudioIn->clear();
const auto inputs = QMediaDevices::audioInputs();
for (const QAudioDevice &device : inputs)
    ui->comboAudioIn->addItem(device.description());
```

Set the SQLite file name with setDatabaseName(), then call open(). Keep connection lifetimes explicit, especially for named connections.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QSqlDatabase db = QSqlDatabase::addDatabase("QSQLITE");
db.setDatabaseName("measurements.db");
if (!db.open())
    qWarning() << db.lastError().text();
```

Use bindValue() or addBindValue() before exec(). Prepared statements separate SQL structure from runtime values.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QSqlQuery query;
query.prepare("INSERT INTO measurements(channel, value) VALUES(:channel, :value)");
query.bindValue(":channel", 3);
query.bindValue(":value", 12.45);
if (!query.exec())
    qWarning() << query.lastError().text();
```

Call exec() first, then iterate while next() returns true. Read individual columns with value().

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QSqlQuery query("SELECT id, name, value FROM measurements");
while (query.next())
{
    qDebug() << query.value(0).toInt()
             << query.value(1).toString()
             << query.value(2).toDouble();
}
```

QSqlQueryModel is suited to arbitrary read-only result sets displayed in views such as QTableView.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *model = new QSqlQueryModel(this);
model->setQuery("SELECT id, name, value FROM measurements");
ui->tableView->setModel(model);
```

Configure edit strategy and filters, then call select(). QSqlTableModel provides an editable model for one database table.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *model = new QSqlTableModel(this);
model->setTable("measurements");
model->setEditStrategy(QSqlTableModel::OnManualSubmit);
model->select();
ui->tableView->setModel(model);
```

QSqlRelationalTableModel extends QSqlTableModel with foreign-key support and can display values from related tables.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
auto *model = new QSqlRelationalTableModel(this);
model->setTable("channels");
model->setRelation(1, QSqlRelation("devices", "id", "name"));
model->select();
ui->tableView->setModel(model);
```

Commit successful changes with commit() or cancel them with rollback(). The retained workflow shows the complete transaction pattern.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QSqlDatabase db = QSqlDatabase::database();
if (db.transaction())
{
    QSqlQuery query(db);
    query.exec("UPDATE counters SET value = value + 1");
    db.commit();
}
else
{
    db.rollback();
}
```

Use QSqlError::text() for a human-readable diagnostic and nativeErrorCode() for backend-specific reporting.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
if (!query.exec())
    qWarning() << query.lastError().text();
```

Use explicit connection names when an application maintains multiple databases or thread-local database connections.

Previous workflow example retained from the original Qt pack:

```cpp
QSqlDatabase db = QSqlDatabase::addDatabase("QSQLITE", "telemetry");
db.setDatabaseName("telemetry.sqlite");
if (!db.open())
    qWarning() << db.lastError().text();
```

